WEBVTT

00:10.788 --> 00:13.493
CLEMENT: Previously
on Justified: City Primeval...

00:13.527 --> 00:14.630
BRYL: Any weapons,
we're bringing them

00:14.663 --> 00:15.765
all back to the station.

00:15.798 --> 00:18.370
You see?
We got a wrecking crew, too.

00:18.403 --> 00:21.242
- Judge's stupid fucking diary
has got to be here somewhere.

00:21.275 --> 00:23.113
TRENNELL: Did you stop
at an antique shop

00:23.146 --> 00:24.750
on the way back?
SWEETY: It's Mansell's.

00:24.783 --> 00:27.556
Thought he was slick
stashing it here.

00:27.589 --> 00:30.729
If this gun
were to show itself,

00:30.762 --> 00:32.666
where does that leave me?
CAROLYN: Turn it in.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.770
Let's get this cracker
off our backs for good.

00:34.803 --> 00:36.574
- You're marrying
Sandy Stanton?

00:36.607 --> 00:38.477
- Sandy's very close
with her brother.

00:38.511 --> 00:40.447
Apparently he wants
to meet me first,

00:40.480 --> 00:41.482
so I say fine.

00:41.516 --> 00:43.821
MAUREEN: Mansell, Stanton,
and the Albanian kid

00:43.854 --> 00:44.823
have been inside nearly
an hour.

00:44.856 --> 00:47.261
Should be wrapping up.
[engine turning over]

00:47.294 --> 00:48.798
[tires squealing]

00:48.831 --> 00:50.100
- All right. Here we go.

00:50.133 --> 00:52.271
[engine revs]

00:52.304 --> 00:54.342
- You need to get
the fuck out of here, bro.

00:54.375 --> 00:57.281
[lively banjo music]

00:57.314 --> 01:02.759
♪ ♪

01:04.395 --> 01:05.799
SANDY: Clement, don't.

01:05.832 --> 01:08.805
[dramatic music]

01:08.838 --> 01:12.478
♪ ♪

01:12.512 --> 01:14.783
- Why don't you get
in that doorway.

01:14.816 --> 01:17.388
♪ ♪

01:17.421 --> 01:18.691
Hmm?

01:20.460 --> 01:23.200
I said move.
[Skender grunts]

01:23.233 --> 01:25.605
♪ ♪

01:25.638 --> 01:26.640
Sandy!

01:26.673 --> 01:28.711
Why don't you do me a favor
and, uh, head over

01:28.744 --> 01:31.517
to that switch, would you?

01:31.550 --> 01:33.621
SANDY:
What are you gonna do to him?

01:33.654 --> 01:35.624
- [speaking Albanian]

01:37.796 --> 01:40.267
CLEMENT: I didn't understand
you, partner.

01:40.300 --> 01:42.271
- You are walking dead man.

01:42.304 --> 01:46.713
CLEMENT: Hmm.
[Skender groaning]

01:48.718 --> 01:51.256
Put your goddamn leg
in the opening.

01:51.289 --> 01:53.293
- [grunts, gasps]

01:53.326 --> 01:54.697
- Or either leg.
I don't care.

01:54.730 --> 01:56.299
SANDY: Babe...

01:56.332 --> 01:59.338
why don't you just punch him
in the face?

01:59.371 --> 02:01.510
- Flip the switch.

02:01.543 --> 02:02.512
- Bullshit!

02:02.545 --> 02:03.781
CLEMENT: Put your leg down,

02:03.814 --> 02:06.386
or I'm gonna splat
your curly flap head

02:06.419 --> 02:07.889
all over this basement.

02:07.922 --> 02:15.170
♪ ♪

02:22.852 --> 02:24.188
CLEMENT:
Sandy...

02:24.221 --> 02:26.694
flip the fucking switch.

02:26.727 --> 02:28.898
♪ ♪

02:28.931 --> 02:31.235
[switch clicks]

02:32.972 --> 02:34.676
[Skender yells]

02:34.709 --> 02:36.847
- I am very disappointed,

02:36.880 --> 02:38.584
but I ain't mad at you,

02:38.617 --> 02:40.287
or I would have pulled
the trigger by now.

02:40.320 --> 02:42.258
You see, when you're lying
in the hospital

02:42.291 --> 02:43.995
with your leg in a cast,

02:44.028 --> 02:45.632
I don't want you to have
any bad thoughts

02:45.665 --> 02:48.871
like wanting to tell the police
or anybody...

02:48.904 --> 02:51.242
because if you do,

02:51.275 --> 02:52.746
I'm gonna come
visit you again...

02:52.779 --> 02:54.248
- [screams]
CLEMENT: And I'm gonna put

02:54.281 --> 02:56.654
your head in there
instead of your leg.

02:56.687 --> 02:57.989
You hear me?
[door clangs]

02:58.022 --> 03:01.563
- [screaming]
- [yelps]

03:03.968 --> 03:05.705
[PA chimes]

03:05.738 --> 03:08.710
[indistinct chatter,
telephones ringing]

03:11.349 --> 03:13.286
BRYL: I'm good.
I'm good, I'm good.

03:13.319 --> 03:14.422
Oh, look who's here.

03:14.455 --> 03:15.992
The Hat shows up
when all the fun's done.

03:16.025 --> 03:17.328
- Heard there was
a fender bender.

03:17.361 --> 03:18.463
- Yeah, these two got
themselves

03:18.496 --> 03:19.867
Beverly Hills Cop'd.

03:19.900 --> 03:21.737
DPD tracked the vehicle
to one of the properties--

03:21.770 --> 03:23.373
a warehouse building
in Corktown.

03:23.406 --> 03:24.510
- So we land, right?

03:24.543 --> 03:26.446
We find a dozen
goddamn Albanians

03:26.479 --> 03:28.450
carrying homeboy
on their shoulders

03:28.483 --> 03:29.887
like Christ off the cross.

03:29.920 --> 03:31.524
We roll up like,
"Hey, guys, what's crackin'?"

03:31.557 --> 03:33.828
They say, "Go fuck yourselves.
He fell down the stairs."

03:33.861 --> 03:35.665
- That clumsy Jesus now?

03:35.698 --> 03:38.738
MAUREEN: Yep, shattered leg,
broken in five places at least.

03:38.771 --> 03:40.407
BRYL:
Get him to implicate Mansell.

03:40.440 --> 03:41.911
Get this prick off the street.

03:41.944 --> 03:43.881
Get him for ag assault
if not murder, right?

03:43.914 --> 03:45.317
Be a star. Come on.

03:45.350 --> 03:46.554
MAUREEN: We don't get
Mansell in lockup,

03:46.587 --> 03:48.290
Albanians are gonna tear
shit up going after him.

03:48.323 --> 03:50.460
- They're gonna try to get
to Mansell through the girl.

03:50.493 --> 03:52.799
- Yeah.
How we feel about that?

03:54.503 --> 03:56.941
- Anybody but us know
about Del Weems' place?

03:56.974 --> 03:58.544
MAUREEN:
Just us chickens.

03:58.577 --> 04:01.951
RAYLAN: So then check out
Sandy's last known address,

04:01.984 --> 04:03.754
put a car on Weems' condo,

04:03.787 --> 04:05.959
and maybe somebody
inside the casino as insurance.

04:05.992 --> 04:07.061
WENDELL:
Already on it.

04:07.094 --> 04:08.531
Skender just got
out of surgery.

04:08.564 --> 04:10.467
- Hey, give me two minutes
with this kid.

04:10.501 --> 04:11.469
WENDELL:
Not gonna talk to you.

04:11.503 --> 04:13.340
Only thing that can make
that boy sing is Toma.

04:13.373 --> 04:14.442
- What's a Toma?

04:14.475 --> 04:16.514
- Toma Kastiot, kid's uncle.

04:16.547 --> 04:17.816
MAUREEN: Calls the shots
for the Albanians

04:17.849 --> 04:18.951
this side of the river.

04:18.984 --> 04:21.022
What Toma says goes.

04:21.055 --> 04:24.328
[soft music]

04:24.361 --> 04:31.309
♪ ♪

04:31.342 --> 04:33.814
[indistinct chatter]

04:33.847 --> 04:36.820
[monitor beeping]

04:36.853 --> 04:41.630
♪ ♪

04:41.663 --> 04:44.335
- Bad step?

04:44.368 --> 04:46.574
I understand,
feeling fragile and all.

04:46.607 --> 04:49.412
Boys in blue
asking a lot of questions,

04:49.445 --> 04:51.082
maybe asking the wrong person.

04:51.115 --> 04:52.819
- Could we have privacy,
please?

04:52.852 --> 04:54.088
This is a family matter.

04:54.121 --> 04:55.625
- I'd like to talk
to your boss.

04:55.658 --> 04:57.629
Think we can arrange that?
- I don't have a boss.

04:57.662 --> 05:01.336
- Everyone has a boss.
Even the boss has a boss.

05:01.369 --> 05:03.975
I got a boss in Miami.
You ever been?

05:04.008 --> 05:06.012
Not a bad place.

05:06.045 --> 05:07.582
I'd like to get back there.

05:07.615 --> 05:10.454
Tell your boss he and I have
a mutual problem

05:10.487 --> 05:13.059
and I believe we can work
for our mutual benefit.

05:13.092 --> 05:16.432
[monitor beeping]

05:18.704 --> 05:21.409
- I'll call him.

05:21.442 --> 05:24.783
- Tell him Deputy U.S. Marshal
Raylan Givens.

05:24.816 --> 05:26.620
Name won't mean
anything to him,

05:26.653 --> 05:30.762
but maybe the part
about it being federal will.

05:30.795 --> 05:33.466
[breathes deeply]

05:33.499 --> 05:36.540
[indistinct chatter]

05:38.142 --> 05:39.513
AGRON:
Nice hat.

05:39.546 --> 05:41.516
Stetson 10X?

05:44.556 --> 05:48.831
- Boss has agreed to talk
about this mutual problems.

05:48.864 --> 05:50.434
- Look at that.

05:50.467 --> 05:52.037
You got a boss after all.

05:52.070 --> 05:53.974
When does this chat happen?

05:56.112 --> 05:57.749
- Mind if I tag along?

05:57.782 --> 06:01.824
Hey, you may need me.
I know a little Albanian.

06:01.857 --> 06:04.796
[upbeat music]

06:04.829 --> 06:10.674
♪ ♪

06:15.483 --> 06:18.758
- [coughing]

06:18.791 --> 06:21.496
CLEMENT:
Damn, woman.

06:21.530 --> 06:22.866
- You want some?

06:22.899 --> 06:24.468
CLEMENT:
You know, you ain't exactly

06:24.502 --> 06:26.807
a walking advertisement
for the shit.

06:26.840 --> 06:30.180
SANDY: [scoffs] Clement,
you're the one got me this way.

06:30.213 --> 06:32.151
- Got you what way, darlin'?

06:32.184 --> 06:35.490
SANDY: Got me what way?
My nerves are shot.

06:35.524 --> 06:37.696
I mean, look,
look at my hand shaking.

06:37.729 --> 06:39.833
- Could be low blood pressure.

06:39.866 --> 06:41.603
SANDY:
Why'd you have to go

06:41.636 --> 06:43.874
and do that
to Skender, Clement?

06:43.907 --> 06:45.945
Hurt his leg that way.
We--we--we never--

06:45.978 --> 06:48.617
we never talked
about doing that.

06:48.650 --> 06:51.022
CLEMENT:
Well, he was provoking me.

06:51.055 --> 06:52.659
SANDY: How?

06:52.692 --> 06:54.830
How--how was
he provoking you so much,

06:54.863 --> 06:56.633
you--you had to go
and smash his leg

06:56.666 --> 06:58.169
with a big, like, door?

06:58.202 --> 07:00.207
CLEMENT: Weird-ass bomb shelter
with no money in it--

07:00.240 --> 07:02.244
it's the perfect place
to store a wad of cash

07:02.277 --> 07:06.018
but this hump uses it
for a mini fridge and a hi-fi.

07:09.959 --> 07:11.797
Ha! Phew.

07:11.830 --> 07:14.101
Got you.

07:14.134 --> 07:15.672
[exhales deeply]

07:15.705 --> 07:18.176
Skender Lollygag ain't nothin'.
He ain't got nobody.

07:18.209 --> 07:21.817
You can forget about that now.
He's old news.

07:21.850 --> 07:23.788
Phew.
You smell that?

07:23.821 --> 07:26.593
- [sniffs]
What? Toast?

07:26.626 --> 07:28.564
- No, baby, money.

07:28.597 --> 07:30.100
You smell money.

07:30.133 --> 07:33.106
[dramatic music]

07:33.139 --> 07:40.153
♪ ♪

07:40.186 --> 07:41.724
PERSON:
Oh.

07:41.757 --> 07:45.230
♪ ♪

07:45.263 --> 07:48.269
[billiard balls clacking]

07:48.302 --> 07:55.651
♪ ♪

07:56.787 --> 07:59.559
[billiard balls clacking]

07:59.592 --> 08:01.630
- Toma Kastiot?

08:01.663 --> 08:03.099
- The same.
You're the marshal?

08:03.132 --> 08:06.005
- Givens. This is
Detective Bryl, Detroit Police.

08:06.038 --> 08:08.176
I got to say, I pictured in my
mind we'd find you

08:08.209 --> 08:09.713
in different digs.

08:09.746 --> 08:12.117
- My own mother lived here.
[billiard balls clack]

08:12.150 --> 08:14.923
I bought the property
when it was distressed.

08:14.956 --> 08:17.862
- Distressed as opposed to now?

08:17.895 --> 08:21.135
- [sighs] The clientele
is very satisfied.

08:21.168 --> 08:24.576
It is a pleasure to give back
to the community.

08:24.609 --> 08:27.582
I hope someday I am cared for

08:27.615 --> 08:30.120
with such, uh, delicacy.

08:30.153 --> 08:31.857
- Yeah.
It's peachy.

08:31.890 --> 08:33.594
Uh, hey, listen, Toma,

08:33.627 --> 08:35.932
sorry to hear
about your nephew there.

08:35.965 --> 08:37.201
Tough luck.

08:37.234 --> 08:39.606
Ah, that leg, ouch.

08:39.639 --> 08:43.045
[Toma groans,
speaking Albanian]

08:48.657 --> 08:50.962
- You want us
to Google that or...

08:50.995 --> 08:53.032
TOMA:
Uh, it means, um,

08:53.065 --> 08:56.774
"You choose your friends,
but family is...

08:56.807 --> 08:58.878
thrust upon you."

08:58.911 --> 09:03.153
My nephew Skender,
he is femije idiot--

09:03.186 --> 09:04.756
an idiot man-child

09:04.789 --> 09:08.664
with an unfortunate
predilection

09:08.697 --> 09:10.167
for bad decisions.

09:10.200 --> 09:11.937
RAYLAN:
Well, here's an opportunity

09:11.970 --> 09:13.941
for him to make
better decisions--

09:13.974 --> 09:16.112
helping us out catching
the dude who did this to him.

09:16.145 --> 09:18.049
TOMA: I-I know
you have come here

09:18.082 --> 09:21.322
to get me to compel Skender
to tell you who has done this

09:21.355 --> 09:23.661
so police can arrest

09:23.694 --> 09:25.965
and serve justice
as you see fit.

09:25.998 --> 09:27.635
- He catches on fast.
[lighter clicking]

09:27.668 --> 09:29.070
TOMA: Mm.

09:31.275 --> 09:35.217
Of course, that justice
is really no justice at all.

09:35.250 --> 09:39.659
It is, uh, only satisfaction
of a mandate

09:39.692 --> 09:41.830
for the appearance of order.

09:41.863 --> 09:45.805
But order and justice,
they are not same thing.

09:45.838 --> 09:47.842
If I wanted to restore order,

09:47.875 --> 09:51.950
I could, of course, instruct
Skender to cooperate.

09:51.983 --> 09:55.357
But I am not interested
in order.

09:55.390 --> 09:57.427
Justice, however...

09:57.460 --> 09:58.964
justice is meted out

09:58.997 --> 10:03.139
in accordance
with the action it remedies.

10:03.172 --> 10:05.811
And in this case...

10:05.844 --> 10:08.016
justice requires
more than the law

10:08.049 --> 10:12.424
is willing or able to provide.

10:12.457 --> 10:14.094
- Well, fuck,
that was a mouthful.

10:14.127 --> 10:16.700
Let me get you to say that
again into my phone.

10:16.733 --> 10:18.269
It'll play great
at your arraignment.

10:18.302 --> 10:20.273
- Mr. Kastiot,

10:20.306 --> 10:23.313
while we understand
where you're coming from

10:23.346 --> 10:25.383
and respect
the personal responsibility

10:25.416 --> 10:28.924
you feel for your nephew,
imbecile or no,

10:28.957 --> 10:31.997
we can't have everybody
in some kind of dogpile

10:32.030 --> 10:34.301
running around
shooting at the wrong people.

10:34.334 --> 10:38.878
- I am not concerned
with wrong people.

10:38.911 --> 10:43.721
Who did this to Skender
did also unto me.

10:43.754 --> 10:46.158
It is same thing.

10:46.191 --> 10:50.000
I will look this shkertate
right in his eye.

10:50.033 --> 10:51.904
- [chuckles]
You hear that, Raylan?

10:51.937 --> 10:53.473
You hear him gazing
into the eyes

10:53.507 --> 10:55.343
of some Russian dipshit

10:55.376 --> 10:59.317
when what he should be looking
for is Clement Mansell.

11:03.192 --> 11:04.896
Oh, come on, this is a secret?

11:04.929 --> 11:06.766
Uh, Toma...

11:08.035 --> 11:10.741
What your nephew
doesn't want anybody to know

11:10.774 --> 11:14.381
is that he got legged
by a fatback Oklahoma dickwad.

11:17.053 --> 11:19.158
RAYLAN: Give me a minute?
BRYL: Sure.

11:19.191 --> 11:22.263
[indistinct PA announcement]

11:24.936 --> 11:27.140
- He was not supposed
to tell me this.

11:28.810 --> 11:30.313
The name is unfamiliar,

11:30.346 --> 11:33.520
but, uh, these things
have a way of changing.

11:33.553 --> 11:35.925
- Look, I can't stop you
from doing

11:35.958 --> 11:37.327
what you're gonna do.

11:37.360 --> 11:39.833
Even sympathize in a way.

11:39.866 --> 11:41.135
But you also need
to understand,

11:41.168 --> 11:43.941
your place in line,
which is to say, me first.

11:43.974 --> 11:46.078
After I'm done,

11:46.111 --> 11:48.449
you can charge the shit heap
with felony assault,

11:48.482 --> 11:51.355
but it ain't gonna mean much
if he's doing life.

11:51.388 --> 11:55.330
You understand what I'm sayin'?
- You tell me to get in line.

11:55.363 --> 11:59.939
I say, "You want him,
you better find him quick,

11:59.972 --> 12:01.409
or he'll be dead."

12:01.442 --> 12:04.081
♪ ♪

12:04.114 --> 12:06.085
Thank you, Marshal Givens.

12:06.118 --> 12:09.224
Perhaps our paths
will cross again.

12:09.257 --> 12:15.805
♪ ♪

12:15.838 --> 12:17.207
BRYL:
You gonna yell at me?

12:17.240 --> 12:18.811
- I've never been
much of a yeller.

12:18.844 --> 12:19.813
BRYL:
'Cause what's not to like?

12:19.846 --> 12:21.082
He's gonna find out anyway.

12:21.115 --> 12:23.086
Either the Albanians lead us
to Mansell,

12:23.119 --> 12:24.990
or they turn him
into little, tiny pieces--

12:25.023 --> 12:26.158
done and done.

12:26.191 --> 12:27.962
- That's an optimistic
point of view.

12:27.995 --> 12:29.899
Another would be
we just put a hit out

12:29.932 --> 12:31.168
on our suspect.

12:31.201 --> 12:33.272
BRYL: Excuse me
for misunderstanding

12:33.305 --> 12:35.911
that you had the willingness
to do what needs getting done.

12:35.944 --> 12:37.381
- I got no problem
getting things done.

12:37.414 --> 12:39.986
I do have a problem
rolling up on Mansell

12:40.019 --> 12:41.857
facedown in a river
shot to death

12:41.890 --> 12:44.863
by some Albanian dipshits...

12:44.896 --> 12:47.134
when what we want

12:47.167 --> 12:49.304
is for the man
to be prosecuted,

12:49.337 --> 12:50.875
forced to answer
for his crimes,

12:50.908 --> 12:54.281
long period of reflection
in a tiny cell.

12:54.314 --> 12:56.953
BRYL: Ah, that's another way
to look at it.

13:03.567 --> 13:05.370
BESNIK:
Let me be the talking one.

13:05.403 --> 13:08.109
- That means someone out there
is not being satisfied, okay?

13:08.142 --> 13:10.013
Smile.
BESNIK: Uh, excuse me, please.

13:10.046 --> 13:11.282
- Yes. One second,
please, gentlemen.

13:11.315 --> 13:13.119
Okay?
Let's get your shoulders up.

13:13.152 --> 13:14.388
You're gonna get
to Friday nights, right?

13:14.421 --> 13:16.125
SERVER: Mm-hmm.
RICK: Okay, I believe you.

13:16.158 --> 13:17.260
Get on it.
Thank you.

13:17.293 --> 13:19.899
Gentlemen, how can I help?

13:19.932 --> 13:21.435
BESNIK: This girl.
- Ah.

13:21.468 --> 13:23.172
BESNIK: She's in
my sister's wedding party,

13:23.205 --> 13:25.878
and she's late for rehearsal,
understand?

13:25.911 --> 13:27.515
Rehearsal starts
in a few minutes,

13:27.548 --> 13:28.617
and still she's not here.

13:28.650 --> 13:31.422
We need to find her,
as she is not picking up phone.

13:31.455 --> 13:32.525
RICK: Mm.

13:32.558 --> 13:34.596
BESNIK: Can you please give us
her address, please?

13:34.629 --> 13:37.067
- I wish I could help you.
I really wish I could.

13:37.100 --> 13:39.606
But, um, that old eye
in the sky right there

13:39.639 --> 13:41.041
wouldn't look so kindly

13:41.074 --> 13:43.279
on me sprinkling
employee information around.

13:43.312 --> 13:45.150
You know, always watching.

13:45.183 --> 13:47.320
- I see.
RICK: Yeah.

13:47.353 --> 13:51.195
- Would a $100 bill
make it easier?

13:51.228 --> 13:53.299
- Ooh, yeah,
it sure would, bro.

13:53.332 --> 13:55.437
But I tell you what--
these guys would not like that.

13:55.470 --> 13:56.907
No.

13:56.940 --> 13:58.209
It's that employee policy.

13:58.242 --> 14:00.313
We can't accept gratuities
on the casino floor.

14:00.346 --> 14:03.319
I'm not happy about it either.

14:03.352 --> 14:05.223
Tell you guys what,

14:05.256 --> 14:07.562
why don't I get you guys
comfortable in the VIP lounge?

14:07.595 --> 14:11.335
First Old Fashioned's on me,
or vodka maybe--whatever.

14:11.368 --> 14:12.505
While you guys are relaxing,

14:12.538 --> 14:15.176
I'm gonna see what I can do
about your little problem.

14:15.209 --> 14:16.646
How does that sound?
PERSON: [clears throat]

14:16.679 --> 14:18.348
Excuse me.

14:20.521 --> 14:21.222
- Sound good?

14:21.255 --> 14:23.359
BESNIK:
That won't be necessary.

14:23.392 --> 14:26.265
I'm sure we can find Sandy's
address, uh, another way.

14:26.298 --> 14:27.635
RICK:
Mm.

14:27.668 --> 14:31.175
Okay, gentlemen.
Good to see you today.

14:31.208 --> 14:33.479
Enjoy your time here, fellas.

14:33.513 --> 14:36.920
Fucking no-neck Albanian
cock-twizzlers.

14:36.953 --> 14:39.626
[whistling]

14:39.659 --> 14:42.931
[distant traffic whirring,
siren wailing]

14:56.124 --> 14:58.229
[exhales sharply]

14:58.262 --> 15:00.233
[screaming]
[engine revs, tires squealing]

15:00.266 --> 15:01.937
BESNIK:
You had chance to be polite.

15:01.970 --> 15:03.974
RICK:
I'm so sorry--

15:04.007 --> 15:05.945
I know! Please stop!

15:05.978 --> 15:07.147
No! Please!

15:07.180 --> 15:10.119
BESNIK:
Agron feels disrespected.

15:10.152 --> 15:12.525
He is sensitive.

15:12.558 --> 15:15.664
RICK: Stop the fucking car!
[tires screech]

15:15.697 --> 15:17.702
Whoa, whoa.

15:17.735 --> 15:19.572
Okay. All right. Okay.

15:19.605 --> 15:26.151
♪ ♪

15:26.184 --> 15:28.557
- No, no! No!

15:28.590 --> 15:30.193
BESNIK: Ah, yes.
RICK: [laughs nervously]

15:30.226 --> 15:32.030
- It's long fall.
- No!

15:32.063 --> 15:33.032
BESNIK:
There are two ways

15:33.065 --> 15:35.003
in which you get back
on the ground from here.

15:35.036 --> 15:37.675
One, Agron lets you go.

15:37.708 --> 15:39.712
And we peel you
off the pavement with a...

15:39.745 --> 15:41.382
How do you say in English?

15:41.415 --> 15:43.286
[speaking Albanian]
BOTH: Blowtorch.

15:43.319 --> 15:44.989
BESNIK:
Blowtorch and spatula.

15:45.022 --> 15:46.458
- Option two.

15:46.491 --> 15:48.396
BESNIK:
Option two--

15:48.429 --> 15:50.200
you give us the address
of Sandy Stanton.

15:50.233 --> 15:51.402
RICK: I don't have
the address, okay?

15:51.435 --> 15:52.572
That's an HR thing.
I don't--[grunts]

15:52.605 --> 15:55.744
BESNIK: Then you go down to HR,
and you get the address.

15:55.777 --> 15:58.282
It's no problem, huh?
Which one you want?

15:58.315 --> 16:01.188
The address or...
[speaking Albanian]

16:01.221 --> 16:02.424
- [whimpers]

16:02.457 --> 16:03.760
- I want you to look at this.

16:03.793 --> 16:05.530
You see how they doin' me?

16:07.500 --> 16:09.438
- It's called an ankle
monitoring bracelet, Tyrone.

16:09.471 --> 16:11.408
- But you see
how tight this shit is?

16:11.441 --> 16:13.714
It itches, too.
Look--look at my foot.

16:13.747 --> 16:16.051
Turnin' all blue and shit.

16:16.084 --> 16:17.320
- Sir...

16:17.353 --> 16:19.324
please.
- [scoffs]

16:19.357 --> 16:21.328
CAROLYN: It's not supposed
to be comfortable.

16:21.361 --> 16:22.765
It's supposed to keep you
out of DDC.

16:22.798 --> 16:24.334
Are you in DDC now?

16:24.367 --> 16:26.338
- What the fuck you giving me
a hard time for?

16:26.371 --> 16:28.242
It's like I ain't got
no friends.

16:28.275 --> 16:29.444
[scoffs]
[door opens]

16:32.083 --> 16:34.454
This cocky motherfucker.

16:35.691 --> 16:37.327
- Don't move.

16:37.360 --> 16:39.330
Don't say shit.

16:40.567 --> 16:43.239
So I'm just gonna go ahead
and assume

16:43.272 --> 16:46.345
you're here
because of Clement Mansell.

16:46.378 --> 16:48.316
RAYLAN:
You're not wrong.

16:48.349 --> 16:49.752
It seems
your knucklehead client

16:49.785 --> 16:52.490
may have crossed a line
with the local Albanian mob.

16:52.524 --> 16:54.127
- So you're here
to question him

16:54.160 --> 16:55.631
about a new complaint,
is that it?

16:55.664 --> 16:56.599
- Uh, no.

16:56.633 --> 17:00.608
The Albanian kid
whose leg he busted up...

17:00.641 --> 17:03.145
he ain't talkin'.

17:03.178 --> 17:04.616
- And so...

17:04.649 --> 17:06.418
RAYLAN: And so
what that means, Carolyn,

17:06.451 --> 17:08.089
is now, as we speak,

17:08.122 --> 17:10.628
hoards of Eastern Europeans
are spreading across Detroit

17:10.661 --> 17:13.265
looking to ixnay your client
and likely Sandy Stanton

17:13.298 --> 17:15.738
and anyone close to him
along the way.

17:15.771 --> 17:18.242
- Why, Marshal...

17:18.275 --> 17:20.781
I think you're trying
to scare me.

17:20.814 --> 17:21.649
- I don't have to.

17:21.683 --> 17:24.388
The Albanians
should already do that.

17:24.421 --> 17:26.225
- Well, they don't.

17:26.258 --> 17:28.095
- Look, it's not for me

17:28.128 --> 17:30.500
to tell you you're in
over your head, Carolyn.

17:30.534 --> 17:32.404
But I ain't been here a week,

17:32.437 --> 17:35.544
and the shit I've seen
has certainly given me pause.

17:35.577 --> 17:39.819
- Marshal, this is my job.

17:39.852 --> 17:43.860
I defend killers.
That's how I make my money.

17:43.893 --> 17:45.564
- I understand that, but--
CAROLYN: And I don't know

17:45.597 --> 17:47.535
whatever it is you got
going on in your head,

17:47.568 --> 17:51.141
but Mansell has the right--
the constitutional right--

17:51.174 --> 17:52.545
to representation.

17:52.578 --> 17:55.584
And I am going to provide
said representation

17:55.617 --> 17:58.690
for as long as he pays me
to do so,

17:58.723 --> 18:00.561
and nobody's gonna scare me
out of doing that.

18:00.594 --> 18:02.163
Anything else you got to ask?

18:02.196 --> 18:05.470
- This is different,
and I think you know that.

18:05.504 --> 18:08.442
[tense music]

18:08.475 --> 18:11.583
♪ ♪

18:11.616 --> 18:13.452
CAROLYN: [sighs]

18:13.485 --> 18:19.164
♪ ♪

18:19.197 --> 18:22.337
What do you want
from me, Marshal?

18:22.370 --> 18:25.309
- All I want is for Mansell

18:25.342 --> 18:28.884
not to do you any harm.

18:28.917 --> 18:31.823
And I'm afraid he might.

18:31.856 --> 18:37.702
♪ ♪

18:37.735 --> 18:42.310
- You do your job,
and I'll do mine.

18:42.343 --> 18:44.247
And we'll see.

18:44.280 --> 18:50.761
♪ ♪

18:50.794 --> 18:52.363
- Okay.

18:53.967 --> 18:55.771
We'll see.

18:55.804 --> 19:02.585
♪ ♪

19:02.618 --> 19:04.321
[indistinct chatter]

19:04.354 --> 19:06.225
- Albanians
are already on the move.

19:06.258 --> 19:09.464
- All right, copy that.
We're on the move.

19:09.497 --> 19:12.370
[indistinct chatter
over police radio]

19:12.403 --> 19:15.778
[car bell dinging]

19:15.811 --> 19:17.247
[dinging stops]

19:17.280 --> 19:20.253
So how'd it go?

19:20.286 --> 19:22.390
[laughing]

19:22.423 --> 19:23.827
That good, huh?

19:23.860 --> 19:25.831
You want some good news?
That was Wendell.

19:25.864 --> 19:27.500
Ball's in play, boss.

19:27.534 --> 19:28.804
Come on, let's move.
[engine turning over]

19:28.837 --> 19:30.674
- Even though
my premium's up to date,

19:30.707 --> 19:32.911
I can't make a claim
'cause why now?

19:34.648 --> 19:37.253
'Cause the police
did the damage?

19:37.286 --> 19:39.892
God damn.
Come on.

19:41.428 --> 19:43.567
I'll call you back.
CLEMENT: God damn.

19:43.600 --> 19:45.269
Smells like bacon in here.

19:45.302 --> 19:46.840
Ooh.
They did a number.

19:46.873 --> 19:49.712
- Yeah, they did a number
on account of you.

19:49.745 --> 19:51.850
- Me?
What'd I do?

19:51.883 --> 19:54.321
- Come in looking for that gun
killed the judge and that girl.

19:54.354 --> 19:55.657
You know anything about that?

19:55.690 --> 19:58.395
- Well, if there was a gun
did something like that

19:58.428 --> 19:59.966
and if I knew
anything about it,

19:59.999 --> 20:01.569
whatever happened,

20:01.602 --> 20:02.905
they didn't find that gun,

20:02.938 --> 20:04.809
'cause baby girl here took it
and sunk it

20:04.842 --> 20:06.946
to the bottom
of the Detroit River.

20:06.979 --> 20:08.583
Am I right, darlin'?

20:08.616 --> 20:11.288
[funk music playing]

20:11.321 --> 20:13.560
- Look, it ain't as easy
as you make it sound--

20:13.593 --> 20:15.931
you know, dump it in the river.

20:15.964 --> 20:17.668
There's people, like,
everywhere.

20:17.701 --> 20:19.304
What if one of them saw me?

20:19.337 --> 20:22.310
"Hey, what are you throwing
in the river?"

20:22.343 --> 20:24.615
CLEMENT: You and that
goddamn weed of yours.

20:24.648 --> 20:27.453
- I wasn't being paranoid,
Clement.

20:27.486 --> 20:29.692
I-I just--I got a bad feeling,

20:29.725 --> 20:34.334
and so I wound up bringing it
back and h-hiding it here.

20:34.367 --> 20:37.340
And--
- I had no idea.

20:37.373 --> 20:38.844
I swear to God, Sweety.

20:38.877 --> 20:43.319
- Or you told baby girl here
to plant that piece in my spot,

20:43.352 --> 20:44.956
set me up to ride your rap.

20:44.989 --> 20:46.860
- Come on,
how long we go back, Sweety?

20:46.893 --> 20:50.601
- H-h-honestly, Sweety,
I only come to put it here

20:50.634 --> 20:52.838
because it's
where he got it from.

20:52.871 --> 20:55.511
♪ ♪

20:55.544 --> 20:58.850
SWEETY: I knew that gun
looked familiar.

20:58.883 --> 21:01.756
CLEMENT: Yeah, it's
a Walther P-38 9 millimeter--

21:01.789 --> 21:04.327
genuine World War II replica.

21:04.360 --> 21:05.864
It's a good gun.

21:05.897 --> 21:08.737
And here you are saying
it looked familiar.

21:08.770 --> 21:12.010
I guess we know why
the cops didn't find it, huh?

21:12.043 --> 21:13.880
- Wait, what?
SWEETY: Yeah, I found it.

21:13.913 --> 21:14.849
I moved it.

21:14.882 --> 21:16.986
And fuck you for the results.

21:17.019 --> 21:18.890
- [scoffs]
Okay.

21:18.923 --> 21:20.894
Little spit and polish,
we all good, right?

21:20.927 --> 21:23.633
- Look, they could've hemmed me
up for life,

21:23.666 --> 21:25.804
drag me
into that interrogation room,

21:25.837 --> 21:27.073
sweat me.

21:27.106 --> 21:28.510
What the hell did you do, man?

21:28.543 --> 21:29.946
- I'm sorry. I am.

21:29.979 --> 21:33.485
It is fucked up
what they done here.

21:33.519 --> 21:35.022
I'd love to make it up to you.

21:35.055 --> 21:38.095
- You can start by paying
to fix all my shit here.

21:38.128 --> 21:40.834
- Can do, mi amigo.

21:40.867 --> 21:42.070
- Hey!

21:42.103 --> 21:45.811
- Now, this a genuine antique
from Albania.

21:45.844 --> 21:49.351
Got to be worth a few grand
at any reasonable pawn shop.

21:49.384 --> 21:51.355
- I love how it's suddenly
yours to hawk,

21:51.388 --> 21:52.791
like you did something
towards getting it.

21:52.824 --> 21:54.795
SWEETY:
This what you got for me?

21:54.828 --> 21:57.568
Some hot old-ass Albanian rock?

21:57.601 --> 21:59.371
CLEMENT:
[chuckles]

21:59.404 --> 22:02.978
Sweety, how much you know
about Judge Alvin Guy?

22:03.011 --> 22:05.049
- I know
he ain't gonna fix my bar.

22:05.082 --> 22:08.556
- Oh, but I think
he just might.

22:08.589 --> 22:11.930
There's money
in these pages, Sweety.

22:11.963 --> 22:14.568
You want to help me count it?

22:14.601 --> 22:21.749
♪ ♪

22:23.853 --> 22:26.960
You got a Stroh's
for an old friend?

22:26.993 --> 22:33.973
♪ ♪

22:36.512 --> 22:39.552
[dog barking]

22:39.585 --> 22:43.727
♪ ♪

22:43.760 --> 22:45.697
AGRON: [grunts]
[barking continues]

22:45.730 --> 22:52.811
♪ ♪

22:58.121 --> 23:00.058
[lock clicks]

23:02.664 --> 23:03.867
- Can I help you?

23:03.900 --> 23:05.771
- Is Sandy home, please?

23:05.804 --> 23:07.140
- Whom should I say is calling?

23:07.173 --> 23:09.512
- Tell her old friends
from college.

23:09.545 --> 23:11.014
- Sandy didn't go to college.

23:11.047 --> 23:14.755
- She worked my cousin's
hot dog stand at varsity games.

23:14.788 --> 23:16.759
- You're gonna have to try her
at work or something

23:16.792 --> 23:18.863
because Sandy's not here.

23:18.896 --> 23:20.801
[door thuds open]
What the fuck?

23:20.834 --> 23:22.972
Get out of here!
Get your hands off of me!

23:23.005 --> 23:26.679
Let me go!
I said let me go!

23:31.689 --> 23:32.925
istant dog barking]

23:32.958 --> 23:34.461
BESNIK: Here's what's going
to happen now.

23:34.494 --> 23:36.131
I'm going to present you
with your cell phone.

23:36.164 --> 23:38.202
You're gonna call Sandy Stanton
and get her to come home.

23:38.235 --> 23:41.743
- Fat chance of that.
- Excuse, please?

23:41.776 --> 23:43.112
- I've been after her for weeks

23:43.145 --> 23:46.118
trying to collect
her half of the rent.

23:46.151 --> 23:48.188
Actually, two things
are gonna happen.

23:48.221 --> 23:50.126
One, you're gonna unzip
my hands

23:50.159 --> 23:51.194
and let me up
out of this chair.

23:51.228 --> 23:54.200
And, two, you're gonna get
the fuck out of my house

23:54.233 --> 23:56.238
while I try and forget
that you were ever here.

23:56.271 --> 24:00.514
- [speaking Albanian]
- [shouting in Lao]

24:00.547 --> 24:03.152
- You're acting very brave.
[barking continues]

24:03.185 --> 24:05.624
But in my experience,
bravery such as this

24:05.657 --> 24:07.661
is an ephemeral thing...

24:07.694 --> 24:11.669
and one subject to conditions
working against its being.

24:11.702 --> 24:13.205
- Yeah, that's really poetic.

24:13.238 --> 24:16.144
Now, seriously,
get the fuck out of my house!

24:16.177 --> 24:18.081
[shouting in Lao]

24:22.557 --> 24:24.961
- [sighs, speaking Albanian]

24:33.679 --> 24:36.118
Do you know what this is?

24:36.151 --> 24:38.890
- Pliers?
BESNIK: [clicks tongue]

24:38.923 --> 24:41.161
It's Albanian tooth extractor.

24:41.194 --> 24:42.931
- Well, what makes it Albanian?

24:42.964 --> 24:45.202
- The fact
that I'm holding it.

24:46.939 --> 24:49.979
[cell phone buzzing]

24:50.012 --> 24:53.285
[indistinct chatter,
music playing softly]

24:53.318 --> 24:57.193
[buzzing continues]

24:57.226 --> 24:58.930
- All right.

24:58.963 --> 25:01.268
And for the gentlemen...
CLEMENT: Yeah. Thank you.

25:01.301 --> 25:03.038
- The steak.

25:03.071 --> 25:04.942
CLEMENT:
[clears throat] Baby...

25:04.975 --> 25:06.077
SANDY:
Mm-hmm?

25:06.111 --> 25:09.017
- Answer it or silence it
and put it in your purse.

25:09.050 --> 25:11.021
But one way or another,
please shut it the fuck up,

25:11.054 --> 25:13.660
because, honestly,
it is ruining the atmosphere.

25:13.693 --> 25:16.699
♪ ♪

25:16.732 --> 25:17.801
- Hello.

25:17.834 --> 25:21.341
- Sandy, it's Hina.
Hi.

25:21.374 --> 25:23.879
- What's wrong?
- It's just these--

25:25.984 --> 25:28.690
See, a water pipe broke
in our apartment,

25:28.723 --> 25:30.660
and, like, all that water,

25:30.693 --> 25:32.363
it's just, like, heading

25:32.396 --> 25:34.300
straight for the closet
in your room.

25:34.333 --> 25:36.004
SANDY: Oh, my God.
Shit. Okay.

25:36.037 --> 25:37.140
Um, we need to leave.

25:37.173 --> 25:39.277
- Hey, hon?
SERVER: Yes?

25:39.310 --> 25:41.716
CLEMENT:
Yeah.

25:41.749 --> 25:43.953
SERVER:
How can I help you?

25:43.986 --> 25:45.857
CLEMENT:
You know what cut this is?

25:45.890 --> 25:48.128
- The Southern Comfort steak?

25:48.161 --> 25:50.332
CLEMENT: Ding, ding, ding.
Ready for Double Jeopardy!

25:50.365 --> 25:52.638
Now, I ordered this steak
black and blue.

25:52.671 --> 25:54.642
Do you know
what black and blue means?

25:54.675 --> 25:57.180
- Means rare?
CLEMENT: Oh, no, ma'am.

25:57.213 --> 26:00.219
It does not mean rare.
I means goddamn bloody red.

26:00.252 --> 26:02.691
So here's
what I want you to do.

26:02.724 --> 26:03.559
I want you to take this.

26:03.593 --> 26:04.862
I want you to throw it
in the trash.

26:04.895 --> 26:06.097
Then I want you to get
your chef,

26:06.130 --> 26:08.402
have another steak,
smack that on the fire,

26:08.435 --> 26:09.337
sing two verses

26:09.370 --> 26:11.709
"Of Dead Leaves
and the Dirty Ground"

26:11.742 --> 26:14.113
flip that sucker,
sing the third verse,

26:14.146 --> 26:16.619
yank it off, plate it,
and bring it back here.

26:16.652 --> 26:19.057
Then I'm gonna cut
into this big-ass hunk

26:19.090 --> 26:20.627
of black and blue meat.

26:20.660 --> 26:23.065
And if I don't hear it moo
in pain...

26:23.098 --> 26:24.400
[clicks tongue]
Then...

26:24.433 --> 26:26.672
we're just gonna start
this all over again.

26:26.705 --> 26:28.676
♪ ♪

26:28.709 --> 26:30.012
HINA: Sandy.

26:30.045 --> 26:32.083
- So where were we?

26:32.116 --> 26:34.354
- W-w-we have to go.
- Why?

26:34.387 --> 26:36.024
- My apartment's
filling up with water

26:36.057 --> 26:37.260
because a pipe broke.
HINA: Sandy?

26:37.293 --> 26:38.863
- Are you the landlord?
HINA: Sandy!

26:38.896 --> 26:41.134
- No, I'm not the landlord.
- Then why do you care?

26:41.167 --> 26:42.871
It's a white man's problem.
HINA: Sandy! Sandy!

26:42.904 --> 26:44.274
- I-I've got my Louboutins
in there.

26:44.307 --> 26:47.046
I've got my Jimmy Choos.
My Balenciaga sock booties.

26:47.079 --> 26:48.182
HINA: Hello?

26:48.215 --> 26:49.818
- Whole new closet
full of shoes--

26:49.851 --> 26:50.953
Daddy'll buy 'em for you.

26:50.987 --> 26:53.325
But we are not leaving here
until I finish my steak.

26:53.358 --> 26:56.264
HINA:
Sandy. Sandy!

26:56.297 --> 26:57.935
SANDY: [sighs]

26:57.968 --> 27:00.272
I'll--I'll be there
as soon as I can.

27:02.042 --> 27:05.049
- You happy?
She's coming.

27:05.082 --> 27:06.886
BESNIK:
I'm happy now.

27:06.919 --> 27:08.355
But in 20 minutes

27:08.388 --> 27:11.161
if Sandy Stanton
has not returned home,

27:11.194 --> 27:14.467
Agron will exact the price
of one of your molars.

27:14.500 --> 27:17.139
[pliers clack]
15 minutes after that,

27:17.172 --> 27:19.210
Agron will take two teeth.
[plier clacking]

27:19.243 --> 27:22.350
Ten minutes more,
he will take three teeth.

27:22.383 --> 27:24.220
[pliers clacking]

27:24.253 --> 27:28.161
- Is like pyramid sets at gym.

27:28.194 --> 27:30.232
BESNIK:
By an hour, he's taking

27:30.265 --> 27:34.340
eight, ten teeth each time.

27:34.373 --> 27:37.013
[chuckles] I hope for the sake
of your, uh--

27:37.046 --> 27:39.317
your pretty smile...

27:39.350 --> 27:41.923
Sandy Stanton comes home soon.

27:41.956 --> 27:43.893
[dark music]

27:43.926 --> 27:45.797
[pliers clank]

27:45.830 --> 27:47.801
♪ ♪

27:47.834 --> 27:49.070
CAROLYN: I got someone

27:49.103 --> 27:51.876
in the county
prosecutor's office...

27:51.909 --> 27:53.979
to talk to me.

27:56.084 --> 27:57.888
- Hope my name didn't come up.

27:57.921 --> 28:00.359
- Mm.
Matter of fact, it did.

28:00.392 --> 28:03.465
[muffled music playing
in the distance]

28:03.498 --> 28:05.937
Way it works is,

28:05.970 --> 28:08.442
you hand over
the murder weapon,

28:08.475 --> 28:13.118
you testify to what you know
about the Wrecking Crew murders

28:13.151 --> 28:15.489
and the judge being killed,

28:15.523 --> 28:18.295
you get immunity
on the Wrecking Crew

28:18.328 --> 28:20.032
and hiding the murder weapon.

28:20.065 --> 28:26.044
♪ ♪

28:26.077 --> 28:28.281
- So, in other words, I snitch.

28:30.385 --> 28:33.225
[lighter clicks]
CAROLYN: Clement Mansell

28:33.258 --> 28:36.464
has held this Wrecking Crew
murder shit

28:36.497 --> 28:39.972
over your head for years.

28:40.005 --> 28:44.815
This--this is how you stop
being his collateral damage.

28:44.848 --> 28:46.084
This.

28:46.117 --> 28:47.521
- I done seen worse
than Clement Mansell.

28:47.554 --> 28:50.259
CAROLYN: [scoffs]
- And I ain't never asked

28:50.292 --> 28:52.430
the system to solve
my problems for me.

28:52.463 --> 28:54.968
I don't want no part
of playing their game.

28:55.001 --> 28:56.806
- Oh, so you gonna play
Mansell's?

28:56.839 --> 28:59.410
Come on, you asked me for this.

28:59.443 --> 29:03.318
- Last time I saw him,
I didn't understand the man.

29:03.351 --> 29:04.788
Now I do.

29:04.821 --> 29:06.424
- Are you sure about that?

29:06.457 --> 29:09.798
- All I know
is I got an opportunity

29:09.831 --> 29:12.136
to get what's coming to me...

29:12.169 --> 29:15.009
and take Mansell down
in the process,

29:15.042 --> 29:17.046
all of which sounds
a damn sight better

29:17.079 --> 29:18.983
than sitting
in some witness box

29:19.016 --> 29:21.454
in open court.

29:21.487 --> 29:22.991
[sniffs]

29:23.024 --> 29:25.429
Nah.
That ain't me, boo.

29:25.462 --> 29:27.299
- What do you mean opportunity?

29:27.332 --> 29:29.003
- You sure you want to hear it?

29:29.036 --> 29:31.976
- Yean, I want to hear it.
Please.

29:32.009 --> 29:33.880
- Gun ain't the only thing
in play

29:33.913 --> 29:36.217
from the night that judge died.

29:37.453 --> 29:40.492
- Do you mean
his little black book?

29:40.526 --> 29:43.198
[dramatic music]

29:43.231 --> 29:45.069
That shit is real?

29:45.102 --> 29:48.543
- Goddamn key to the city.

29:48.576 --> 29:50.980
Enough dirt in that book

29:51.013 --> 29:53.251
to make some real moves...

29:53.284 --> 29:54.621
the kind of moves

29:54.654 --> 29:57.126
that could put you
in that judge's seat...

29:57.159 --> 29:59.297
♪ ♪

29:59.330 --> 30:01.501
If that's what you wanted.

30:01.535 --> 30:04.140
♪ ♪

30:04.173 --> 30:07.213
- [sighs]

30:07.246 --> 30:11.054
Wading around
in murky waters like this,

30:11.087 --> 30:13.091
that's how you get bit.

30:13.124 --> 30:15.329
♪ ♪

30:15.362 --> 30:17.901
Are you sure you want to--

30:17.934 --> 30:20.172
you want to fuck around
with this guy?

30:20.205 --> 30:22.944
You want to fuck around
with this killer?

30:22.977 --> 30:25.950
- I'm tired of waiting around
for the right thing to happen.

30:25.983 --> 30:32.898
♪ ♪

30:32.931 --> 30:36.137
[dog barking]
- Nice neighborhood.

30:36.170 --> 30:38.375
She's a striver,
it would appear.

30:38.408 --> 30:40.145
RAYLAN:
Recognize the car out front?

30:40.178 --> 30:41.882
- I hope they don't fuck
like they park.

30:41.915 --> 30:43.653
They'd never get it in.
[car door opens]

30:43.686 --> 30:46.625
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where you going, cowboy?

30:46.658 --> 30:48.428
- Stretch my legs,
go for a walk.

30:48.461 --> 30:51.434
What's it look like I'm doing?
BRYL: You sure about this?

30:51.467 --> 30:53.940
'Cause, again,
the beauty of this

30:53.973 --> 30:56.377
is we just wait
till Mansell shows up.

30:56.410 --> 30:58.148
Guns start blazing,

30:58.181 --> 31:00.486
we stroll on in there,
save the day.

31:00.520 --> 31:02.223
Shazam.

31:02.256 --> 31:04.661
- Yeah, I'm going in.

31:04.694 --> 31:06.531
- Fuck me.

31:10.005 --> 31:11.274
[dog barking]

31:11.307 --> 31:12.611
RAYLAN: You want the front
or the back?

31:12.644 --> 31:14.648
BRYL: Since we're gonna
fuck it all up anyway,

31:14.681 --> 31:15.683
I'll take the front.

31:15.716 --> 31:17.687
[barking continues]

31:17.720 --> 31:24.466
♪ ♪

31:46.010 --> 31:48.649
[Hina whimpers, screaming]

31:50.385 --> 31:52.323
RAYLAN:
U.S. Marshals. Hands up.

31:52.356 --> 31:54.260
BRYL:
Don't move, motherfucker!

31:54.293 --> 31:55.597
[Hina whimpers]

31:55.630 --> 31:58.401
RAYLAN: Lose it...
right now, slow.

31:58.434 --> 32:01.675
[barking continues,
Hina crying]

32:01.708 --> 32:04.080
Slow.

32:04.113 --> 32:08.354
[Hina speaking Lao]

32:10.158 --> 32:11.494
Okay.

32:11.528 --> 32:14.000
Now, we're all gonna be
real easy for a minute.

32:14.033 --> 32:17.540
[Hina cries, shouts]

32:19.343 --> 32:22.049
BRYL:
God damn it!

32:22.082 --> 32:23.653
Fuck!

32:23.686 --> 32:26.692
Stop! Police!
Drop the weapon.

32:26.725 --> 32:30.299
[gunshots]

32:30.332 --> 32:33.038
[barking continues]

32:33.071 --> 32:34.974
Clear!
Shots fired!

32:38.682 --> 32:39.785
- Don't.

32:39.818 --> 32:43.291
♪ ♪

32:43.324 --> 32:46.264
[barking continues]

32:46.297 --> 32:53.411
♪ ♪

32:56.785 --> 32:59.190
- Holy shit.

32:59.223 --> 33:01.227
- [speaking Albanian]

33:01.260 --> 33:03.465
[shouting in Albanian]

33:03.498 --> 33:06.371
♪ ♪

33:06.404 --> 33:09.778
[shouts in Albanian]

33:09.811 --> 33:16.591
♪ ♪

33:21.802 --> 33:25.042
[screaming]

33:25.075 --> 33:32.055
♪ ♪

33:44.246 --> 33:45.550
- Night, Hector.

33:45.583 --> 33:47.486
HECTOR:
You get any dinner?

33:47.520 --> 33:50.727
- I'll pick up some later.
- All right.

33:50.760 --> 33:53.832
[distant siren wailing]

34:02.149 --> 34:05.088
[engine turning over]

34:22.255 --> 34:24.528
[engine turning over]

34:24.561 --> 34:27.499
[suspenseful music]

34:27.533 --> 34:30.105
♪ ♪

34:30.138 --> 34:33.579
[tires squealing]

34:33.612 --> 34:40.592
♪ ♪

34:49.309 --> 34:50.646
- [sighs]

34:50.679 --> 34:57.660
♪ ♪

34:57.693 --> 35:01.735
[line trilling]

35:01.768 --> 35:04.473
Hey, it's Carolyn Wilder.

35:04.507 --> 35:11.554
♪ ♪

35:32.229 --> 35:34.668
[window squeaking]

35:34.701 --> 35:36.505
- Gentlemen...

35:36.538 --> 35:39.911
time to head back to the Venus,
check in with the boss.

35:39.944 --> 35:42.550
I think you'll find
there's been a shake-up

35:42.583 --> 35:44.420
in personnel.

35:44.453 --> 35:47.292
But just so we're clear,
whatever you've been told,

35:47.325 --> 35:50.833
this particular lawyer
is off-limits.

35:50.866 --> 35:53.873
Run along, tell Toma
Raylan Givens said so.

35:53.906 --> 35:57.814
And if he's got a problem
with that, he can come find me.

35:57.847 --> 35:59.818
That's it.
The conversation's over.

35:59.851 --> 36:02.757
I say have a good night.
You two drive away.

36:02.790 --> 36:07.266
[siren wailing]

36:07.299 --> 36:09.169
[shifter clacks]

36:24.032 --> 36:28.709
- I have never in my life
been more happy to see a cop.

36:28.742 --> 36:31.548
- Just come
from Sandy Stanton's place.

36:31.581 --> 36:32.717
Caught two of them there

36:32.750 --> 36:34.588
pulling her roommate's
teeth out.

36:34.621 --> 36:35.823
- Jesus.

36:35.856 --> 36:37.326
RAYLAN:
Bryl killed one of them.

36:37.359 --> 36:39.564
Other one's downtown.

36:39.597 --> 36:41.033
All happened
a couple hours ago,

36:41.066 --> 36:42.937
and already here they are
at your office

36:42.970 --> 36:45.610
waiting to follow you home.

36:45.643 --> 36:48.281
- [sighs]

36:48.314 --> 36:49.851
Well, I'm sure glad

36:49.884 --> 36:52.356
that you sent them
on their way.

36:52.389 --> 36:53.224
- They'll be back.

36:53.258 --> 36:54.961
Sooner or later,
they'll find your house.

36:54.994 --> 36:56.732
- Well, I can handle things
at my house.

36:56.765 --> 36:57.700
RAYLAN:
You ain't gonna have to.

36:57.734 --> 36:59.805
We'll have someone there
keeping an eye out.

36:59.838 --> 37:01.608
- I'm not asking you
to do that.

37:01.641 --> 37:03.044
RAYLAN:
It ain't your decision.

37:03.077 --> 37:06.284
And it ain't a favor
for me to grant.

37:06.317 --> 37:09.724
You understand, you are a value
to this investigation.

37:09.757 --> 37:10.860
- And what
if I don't want somebody

37:10.893 --> 37:11.995
sitting outside my house?

37:12.028 --> 37:14.400
- Take it up with the judge,
I guess.

37:14.433 --> 37:15.837
- You're not hearing me,
Marshal.

37:15.870 --> 37:19.711
- Hey, I'm just doing my job.

37:19.744 --> 37:23.519
- Well, you do
what you have to do.

37:23.552 --> 37:24.887
- Have a good night.

37:33.004 --> 37:36.077
- There he is.
Get in here.

37:36.110 --> 37:37.714
Hey.

37:37.747 --> 37:39.851
Yeah.
SWEETY: This your new drip?

37:39.884 --> 37:41.688
- Ah, you know,
I wasn't too sure about it

37:41.721 --> 37:44.794
when I put it on, but turns out
the damn thing's comfy.

37:44.827 --> 37:46.999
I might have to keep it.

37:47.032 --> 37:49.905
Let me pour you one.
We got to celebrate.

37:49.938 --> 37:52.075
- Lofty perch you got here.
[glasses clink]

37:52.108 --> 37:54.446
- Yeah. Old Del's got
questionable taste

37:54.479 --> 37:55.883
in clothing and decor,

37:55.916 --> 37:59.591
but, you know, he makes up
for it in location and liquor.

37:59.624 --> 38:00.626
[bottle thuds]

38:00.659 --> 38:02.630
You could be up in a crib
like this, Sweety--

38:02.663 --> 38:04.601
man of your talent, stature.

38:04.634 --> 38:06.003
Ought to be out
living your dream

38:06.036 --> 38:08.041
instead of counting pennies.

38:08.074 --> 38:09.811
- You keep blowing smoke
up my ass,

38:09.844 --> 38:11.347
I'm gonna be burping
that shit up.

38:11.380 --> 38:12.884
- No smoke, my friend.

38:12.917 --> 38:15.055
I want you to do this,
simple as that.

38:15.088 --> 38:17.927
I messed up.
You got done wrong.

38:17.960 --> 38:20.633
So let's do this thing
the right way.

38:20.666 --> 38:22.704
- Yeah?

38:22.737 --> 38:24.541
How so?
CLEMENT: You know this town.

38:24.574 --> 38:27.412
You know the names
in that judge's little book.

38:27.445 --> 38:28.816
You know how we get at them,

38:28.849 --> 38:31.420
how to let them know
we mean business.

38:31.453 --> 38:33.926
[chuckles] You're
the full package, Sweety.

38:33.959 --> 38:36.030
- So I've been told.

38:36.063 --> 38:38.468
CLEMENT:
So get on board, man.

38:38.501 --> 38:42.042
Split this straight down
the middle, 50-50.

38:42.075 --> 38:44.881
Partners making
dreams come true.

38:46.618 --> 38:48.487
- This is a nice view.

38:50.793 --> 38:52.797
- Yeah, me and Sandy,
we were talking.

38:52.830 --> 38:54.601
We get this job did,

38:54.634 --> 38:57.105
we take a little
extended vacation, maybe Aruba.

38:57.138 --> 39:01.882
Oh. You and Trennell,
y'all should come along.

39:01.915 --> 39:03.151
- Aruba, huh?

39:03.184 --> 39:05.690
- I mean, wherever,
my dude, right?

39:05.723 --> 39:08.461
Aruba?
Jamaica?

39:08.494 --> 39:10.900
[Sweety chuckles]

39:10.933 --> 39:12.937
♪ Ooh, I want to take you ♪

39:12.970 --> 39:15.610
♪ To Bermuda, Bahama ♪

39:15.643 --> 39:17.914
♪ Come on, pretty mama ♪

39:17.947 --> 39:20.418
♪ Key Largo, Montego ♪
- What the fuck, Clement?

39:20.451 --> 39:24.159
CLEMENT: ♪ Baby, why don't
we go down to Kokomo? ♪

39:24.192 --> 39:28.736
♪ We'll get there fast,
and then we'll take it slow ♪

39:28.769 --> 39:30.472
♪ That's where ♪

39:30.506 --> 39:32.877
♪ We want to go ♪
- Jesus F. Christ.

39:32.910 --> 39:35.683
CLEMENT:
♪ Way down in Kokomo ♪

39:35.716 --> 39:38.756
SINGER: ♪ Martinique,
that Montserrat mystique ♪

39:38.789 --> 39:43.131
♪ We'll put out to sea ♪

39:43.164 --> 39:47.774
♪ And we'll perfect
our chemistry ♪

39:47.807 --> 39:50.078
♪ By and by, we'll defy ♪

39:50.111 --> 39:52.817
♪ A little bit of gravity ♪

39:52.850 --> 39:56.023
♪ ♪

39:56.056 --> 40:00.031
♪ Afternoon delight ♪

40:00.064 --> 40:04.039
♪ Cocktails
and moonlit nights ♪

40:04.072 --> 40:06.177
♪ That dreamy look
in your eye ♪

40:06.210 --> 40:10.586
♪ Give me
a tropical contact high ♪

40:10.619 --> 40:12.456
♪ Way down in Kokomo ♪

40:12.489 --> 40:16.097
♪ Aruba, Jamaica,
ooh, I want to take you ♪

40:16.130 --> 40:20.138
♪ To Bermuda, Bahama,
come on, pretty mama ♪

40:20.171 --> 40:22.510
♪ Key Largo, Montego,
baby, why don't we go ♪

40:22.543 --> 40:26.718
♪ Ooh, I want to take you
down to Kokomo ♪

40:26.751 --> 40:28.187
♪ We'll get there fast ♪

40:28.220 --> 40:30.993
♪ And then we'll take it slow ♪

40:31.026 --> 40:35.201
♪ That's where we want to go ♪

40:35.234 --> 40:37.707
♪ Way down in Kokomo ♪

40:37.740 --> 40:39.176
♪ Port au Prince... ♪

40:39.209 --> 40:41.080
CAROLYN:
The whole Detroit Police

40:41.113 --> 40:43.251
keeping an eye out...

40:43.284 --> 40:45.121
and look here.

40:45.154 --> 40:47.660
RAYLAN: Appears I drew
the short straw.

40:47.693 --> 40:49.063
- Oh-ho.

40:49.096 --> 40:52.135
- I can phone in a replacement
if you'd prefer.

40:55.208 --> 40:56.944
Not bad.

41:06.330 --> 41:08.902
CAROLYN: Hold on to that
for me, sir.

41:16.584 --> 41:19.289
Client gave it to me.

41:19.322 --> 41:21.762
Thought it might be
right about up your alley.

41:21.795 --> 41:24.065
[liquor pouring]

41:26.838 --> 41:28.608
- You figured right.

41:33.718 --> 41:36.157
Ahh.

41:36.190 --> 41:39.163
CAROLYN:
I never get used to this.

41:39.196 --> 41:41.601
RAYLAN: Goes down better
if you put

41:41.634 --> 41:43.839
a little sparkler in it
and set it on fire.

41:43.872 --> 41:46.945
CAROLYN:
[chuckles]

41:46.978 --> 41:48.849
Yeah. That's right.

41:48.882 --> 41:50.886
Where is your kid?

41:50.919 --> 41:52.189
You locked her up in a room

41:52.222 --> 41:54.326
so you could skulk
about the hood?

41:54.359 --> 41:57.667
- She's back in Miami
with her mother.

41:57.700 --> 41:59.002
CAROLYN:
Oh.

41:59.035 --> 42:03.211
So you're free, unencumbered,

42:03.244 --> 42:06.852
and yet you're spending it
parked out here

42:06.885 --> 42:08.956
by yourself.

42:08.989 --> 42:11.026
RAYLAN:
Well, you're with me now.

42:11.059 --> 42:13.665
Not by myself anymore.

42:18.875 --> 42:21.180
- Just so we're clear,

42:21.213 --> 42:23.986
this does not change
where we stand

42:24.019 --> 42:25.623
vis-à-vis my client.

42:25.656 --> 42:26.691
- Just so we're clear,

42:26.725 --> 42:30.866
I didn't come here
to talk about Clement Mansell.

42:30.899 --> 42:33.004
CAROLYN:
All right.

42:33.037 --> 42:35.375
RAYLAN:
Hmm.

42:35.408 --> 42:40.351
- So you're just gonna stay
out here all night...

42:40.384 --> 42:42.021
by yourself?

42:43.892 --> 42:46.063
- Hadn't planned
that far ahead.

42:46.096 --> 42:47.934
Kind of just...

42:47.967 --> 42:50.840
playing it as it went.

42:50.873 --> 42:54.046
- Shooting from the hip?

42:54.079 --> 42:56.349
- Something like that.
